00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,719
- About what?
- The war.

245
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,876
- The war?
- Yes.

246
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:04,913
I have a feeling I can help.

247
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,878
I doubt it

248
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:10,036
It's over.

249
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,839
- What are you doing?
- You told me to lay out...

250
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:21,999
All right, I'll do it. Get on the phone
and find a place for those women. - Yes, Sir.

253
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:31,996
Come In.

254
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:37,228
- Mr. Talbot?
- Yes.

255
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:41,800
- I was wondering if we could talk now?
- I'm...

256
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,797
Please, It's terribly important

257
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,638
Why don’t you sit down?

258
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:48,877
No, no, not there. On the couch.

259
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:50,672
What do you mean?

260
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:53,394
Now try and relax. Lie down.

261
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:56,990
- Lie down?
- It's for your own good.

262
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,997
There.

263
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:06,477
Really, Mr. Talbot
You must try and relax.

264
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:15,631
Now. Where would you like to begin?

265
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:22,517
I really don't know.
Where would you suggest?

266
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,551
Well...

267
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:27,797
Let's start with... the war.

268
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:33,032
That war really... bothers you,
doesn't it?

269
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:36,156
You were In the Army.

270
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:39,799
I thought I was In the Navy.

271
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,912
No, you were In the Army.

272
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:48,240
Standing sentry duty...
at an ammunition dump

273
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:51,000
that blew up.

274
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,909
Do you remember that?

275
00:24:57,920 --> 00:25:02,118
All I remember Is
being officer In a PT boat.

276
00:25:02,320 --> 00:25:06,632
Don’t you see? That’s your subconscious
substituting fantasy for fact.

277
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:07,795
Look...

278
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,912
That’s why you think
you own this place.

279
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,912
Don't I?

280
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:22,158
No. Really, Mr. Talbot
You must face reality.

281
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:26,148
Your family lost this house,
Mr. Cavell bought it,

282
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:28,954
turned it Into a hotel.

283
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:35,473
- A hotel?

284
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:47,479
- La Dolce Vista?
- That's right.

285
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:54,517
- People pay him to stay here?
- Yes.

286
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,513
It's a hotel.

287
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:01,633
You don't know how happy
you've made me. I knew I could help you.

288
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:03,831
Oh, you have.

289
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:06,713
Suddenly, all the pieces
have fallen Into place.

290
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:09,559
Mr. Cavell will be so thrilled
you've recovered.

291
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:11,796
- I'll go tell him.
- No, no, no.

292
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,796
Let me tell him.

294
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:38,674
You can tell Maria to stop praying.

295
00:26:38,880 --> 00:26:41,553
Her friend didn't survive the crisis.

296
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:46,919
Excuse me. I have some duties.
A major-domo's day Is never done.

297
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:48,872
Yours Is.

298
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:52,117
Don't think of your self as a major-domo.

299
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:55,312
More like a sentry
at an ammunition dump

300
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:57,750
that's about to blow up.

301
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:02,911
- Your room or mine?
- Yours.

302
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:17,759
- You're a thief.
- Yes, sir.

303
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:19,154
- And a liar.
- Yes, sir.

304
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:20,952
Completely untrustworthy.

305
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:23,833
Thief and a liar, yes.
But not untrustworthy.

306
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:26,918
I really don't think this is the proper time
to talk the matter out

307
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:30,112
Not while your mind is bristling
with negative thoughts.

308
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:33,073
I haven’t even begun to bristle.

309
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:37,751
- Turning my house Into a hotel.
- How easy for you to say "my house".

310
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:40,474
- You're never here.
- What's that to do with it?

311
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:44,195
When her windows are stuck do you care?
No, you're In New York

312
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,391
I, Maurice, have to unstick them.

313
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:49,831
On a cold night when
her radiators knock are you here?

314
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,598
No, I have to warm them up.

315
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:55,679
And when her plumbing goes out
who's there to unclog her? Maurice.

316
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:59,316
You're like a husband who's only
with his wife one month a year.

317
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:02,876
It's the man who's with her the rest
of the year deserves the credit

318
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:06,470
Well, I don’t care for
what you’ve turned my wife Into.

319
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:09,240
- What have I done with the profit?
- That's a good question.

320
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:12,876
Painted her. Put In a new garden wall,
a fountain, a patio.

321
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:16,072
- I even replenished the wine cellar.
- Not to mention your wallet.

322
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:22,077
Any personal gain
was of secondary importance.

323
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:25,556
Your smile of appreciation
when you came here every year.

324
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:28,797
That was my real... my real reward.

325
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:37,958
Tell your guests
to find themselves another hotel.

326
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:41,596
As for you and your accomplices,
pack your bags and leave in the morning.

327
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:45,031
Sir, I wish you'd sleep
on that decision.

328
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:48,471
Tomorrow, we'll probably both
laugh about this matter.

329
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:51,797
We might both be laughing.
But not In the same house.

330
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:55,436
Sir, may I please ask one last favor?

331
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:59,474
Margaret, the chaperone. She's been
coming with tourists for some time.

332
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:03,150
We've become rather close,
even made plans for the future.

333
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,669
She thinks I'm the owner.

334
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:09,236
Will you please let me explain it to her
In my own way?

335
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:13,399
All right. But I have the feeling
I'm not doing Margaret any favor.

336
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:15,591
Thank you. I'll talk to her right away.

337
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:18,553
We should be leaving in about half an hour to 
pick up Ms. Fellini at the station.

338
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:20,034
I'll pick her up my self.

339
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:24,119
Please, sir. As long as I'm here,
I'd like to attend to my duties.

340
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:29,068
Just for my own Information,

341
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:31,236
how long has this been a hotel?

342
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,436
Six years.

343
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:40,754
it was a fine hotel, sir,
with a Triple A rating.

344
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:43,235
Conrad Hilton
would have been proud to own it

345
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:46,354
I'm surprised you didn't sell it to him.

346
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:49,036
The deed Is In your name.

347
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:56,508
Che piacere rivederla, signorina.

348
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:59,109
- Grazie Maurice.
- What did he say?

349
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:02,278
- That It's nice to see me.
- Oh.

350
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:05,358
- La trovo bene, Maurice.
- Lisa, please.

351
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:08,791
- Don't pat the servants.
- Maurice? He's more than a servant

352
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:13,039
Yes, I found that out today.
Keep your eyes on the road.

353
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:15,629
Robert, you're terribly sharp
with Maurice.

354
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:18,195
What's wrong?

355
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:22,678
How would you feel if you found out
Brutus was your major-domo?

356
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:27,158
Lucrezia Borgia your cook
and Benedict Arnold your upstairs maid?

357
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:28,713
Cos'hal combinato?

358
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:31,992
Questa villa resta vuota
Un dici mes al l'anno.

359
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:37,194
Al lora mi son detto: "Che peccato,
perché non convertirla In un albergo?"

360
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:40,517
- A hotel
- Filled with tourists.

361
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:43,996
Look... He even advertises.

362
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:46,077
Don't laugh, you'll encourage him.

363
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:49,875
C'é solo una povera vecchia
con sei hambin Indifes.

364
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:52,435
E lui Il butta fuori, sulla strada.

365
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:54,232
- È vero?
- È vero.

366
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:55,998
- I can't believe it
- What?

367
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:58,953
That you could be so cruel,
to throw out on the street

368
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:02,789
an old woman
and six helpless children.

369
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,878
- They’re not children, they're...
- What?

370
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:10,435
- Not children.
- Chie devo solo di lasciarli una notte.

371
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:13,074
Se ne vada domattina.

372
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:16,909
Why can’t they stay one night?
They are leaving In the morning.

373
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:21,352
I don't want anybody there tonight.
Do you?

374
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:25,519
Roberto, what can one night hurt?

375
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:28,473
- Ha ragione, cosa importa...
- You keep out of this.

376
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:32,309
- Don’t you listen to him.
- I've never seen you like this before.

377
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:36,433
- You're upset.
- Of course I'm upset.

378
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:38,631
It's 10 months since we had seen each other.

379
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:42,549
- Whose fault Is that?
- Mi fa male sentirvi litigare.

380
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:47,311
Isn't he sweet?
He said it upsets him to hear us argue.

381
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:51,069
There’s nothing to argue about
He's already told them to leave.

382
00:31:55,440 --> 00:32:00,275
You did tell your friend Margaret,
didn’t you?

383
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:04,155
Come potevo? Stava facendo Il bagno,
non siamo poi così tanto amici.

384
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:07,396
Don’t talk to her, talk to me.

385
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:11,639
- What's the big joke?
- He said, how could he tell her?

386
00:32:11,840 --> 00:32:15,674
She was taking a bath,
and they're not that friendly.

387
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:18,352
I don't think that's funny.

388
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:22,633
Mi  preoccupa.
Ha perso tutto Il suo spirito.

389
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:27,231
He said he's worried about you.
You've lost your sense of humour.

390
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:30,671
Well, I'll get it back when he leaves.

391
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:44,473
I don't think you should go In with me.

392
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:46,432
Why not?

393
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:52,237
The hotel guests.
How will it look if we come In together?

394
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:57,514
All right. I'll park the car and come In
through the servants' entrance.

395
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:03,271
I wouldn't want you
to lose your Triple A rating.

397
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:28,474
Oh, Miss Allison. Signorina Fellini.

398
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:30,830
- Buon giorno .
- Good afternoon.

399
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:37,589
- Who's she?
- A school teacher.

400
00:33:39,520 --> 00:33:41,954
She doesn't look like a school teacher.

401
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:44,754
Margaret, If beauty
symbolizes occupation,

402
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:47,554
I would mistake you for a star 
from the cinema

403
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:49,318
Maurice

406
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:17,953
- Oh, not now.
- Why not?

407
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:20,549
- She's taking a shower.
- Who Is?

408
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:22,910
- Sandy.
- Sandy?

409
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:25,998
The girl with whom I share 
the room.

410
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:32,514
- You're rooming with someone?


411
00:34:32,720 --> 00:34:35,632
- I'll kill that Maurice.
- It's not his fault

412
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:40,470
If he moved everyone around so I could
be alone In the room next to yours,

413
00:34:40,680 --> 00:34:42,352
how would it look?

414
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:44,516
You'd better leave.

415
00:34:46,160 --> 00:34:50,312
- We'll have dinner on my terrace.
- There Isn't room for nine people.

416
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:54,274
- What nine people?
- They’ll suspect if we eat alone.

417
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:56,948
Hurry, she might see you.

418
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:58,832
Be careful.

419
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,556
What am I sneaking around for?
It's my...

420
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:04,751
- Shhi
...house.

421
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:13,589


422
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:23,431
You'd better wait

423
00:36:26,200 --> 00:36:30,478
Miss Allison hasn't made her bed-check.
And she's already suspicious.

424
00:36:32,120 --> 00:36:34,998
- Of what?
- You and Mr. Talbot

425
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:39,875
- What about us?
- Don’t get me wrong.

426
00:36:40,080 --> 00:36:43,152
I think It's terribly exciting.
All the girls do.

427
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:46,272
Two people In love.
In a romantic place like this.

428
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:49,995
It's the dreamiest thing
I've ever heard of.

429
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:54,079
I'm going downstairs
to get some warm milk.

430
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:56,555
Warm milk?

431
00:36:57,880 --> 00:37:01,429
He looks more like
the champagne type to me.

432
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:20,314
Good night, girls. Lights out now.

433
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:23,194
Err...

434
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:27,996
I was just going downstairs...
to get some warm milk.

436
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:07,676
I got the warm milk.

437
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:27,277
- Sandy.
- Yes, ma'am.

438
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:29,596
Lights out now.

439
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:33,957
- Good night, girls.
- Good night.

440
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:41,479
She'll be asleep In ten minutes.

441
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:43,875
So will I.

442
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:47,870
But he's waiting for you.
I can hear the music.

443
00:38:48,080 --> 00:38:52,870
I really don't know where
a girl your age gets Ideas like that

444
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:57,119
I have no Intention
of going to Mr. Talbot's room.

445
00:38:57,320 --> 00:38:58,753
I'm going...

446
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:03,511
Yes, I'm going to finish my milk
and go to sleep.

451
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:30,310
Good morning.

452
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:32,829
- Morning?

453
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:38,748
- What happened to last night?
- Everybody looked suspicious.

454
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:41,030
And Sandy knew about us.

455
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:44,915
I couldn't leave.
it would've been too obvious.

456
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:49,318
Sandy seems to know about everything.
Now I know what she's doing In Europe.

457
00:40:49,520 --> 00:40:52,876
Her neighbors
decided to chip In and send her.

459
00:40:55,960 --> 00:40:59,270
- What's that?
- They’re getting ready to leave.

460
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:00,595
Good.

461
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:04,319
I promised to come down
and say goodbye.

462
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:06,750
Oh, send them a letter.

463
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:10,509
- It'll only take a minute
- No, Lisa, come on.

464
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:14,793
- I think you should come and say goodbye too.
- I'll wave to them from the terrace.

465
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:16,991
Teenagers are like the H-bomb.

466
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:21,478
When they go off, It's much better
to observe them from a distance.

467
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:40,079
- Bye, Mr. Talbot
- Bye

468
00:41:40,280 --> 00:41:43,875
- Goodbye, Mr. Talbot
- Bye, Mr. Talbot

469
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:47,354
Good morning, sir.
Your orange juice.

470
00:41:47,560 --> 00:41:53,271
Not orange juice, Maurice, champagne.
It's a special occasion.

471
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:55,436
The hotel Is closing,

472
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:57,517
you're packing,

473
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:59,950
and the guests are leaving.

474
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:04,950
How often does a man get rid
of all his troubles at the same time?

475
00:42:06,520 --> 00:42:08,112
Oh, what's the matter?

477
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:17,075
I don't understand, Miss Allison.
What are you doing In traction?

478
00:42:18,080 --> 00:42:20,640
Slipped on a champagne cork?

479
00:42:20,840 --> 00:42:25,755
it was an accident
I've sprung my sacroiliac.

480
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:30,192
Mm? No, I've had this happen before.

481
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:34,393
Don't worry, I'll be absolutely splendid
by the morning.

482
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:38,196
The girls can’t go without her.

483
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:42,511
You will have to let them stay 
until tomorrow

484
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:55,438
You wouldn’t think a cork this small
could lay out woman that big.

485
00:42:56,840 --> 00:43:01,197
Maria, move Miss Fellini's luggage
into Miss Allison room.

486
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:02,958
- Teresa and...
- Milena, sir.

487
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:05,594
Start making sandwiches. Lots of them.

488
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:08,473
Mr. Cavell will need
all of his strength.

489
00:43:08,680 --> 00:43:13,310
- Where am I going?
- On a long hike. With the girls.

490
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:16,512
You're going to show them Italy.
All of it.

491
00:43:16,720 --> 00:43:19,029
if you run out of Italy,
show them Sicily.

492
00:43:19,240 --> 00:43:21,629
That ought to take you all the day.

493
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:24,070
And a good part of the night, sir.

494
00:43:24,280 --> 00:43:26,555
I'm glad we understand each other.

495
00:43:39,680 --> 00:43:42,433
It's a shame the girls
