and the enemy doesn't follow you,

1246
01:40:08,360 --> 01:40:10,749
you've got to turn around and attack.

1247
01:40:10,960 --> 01:40:13,679
What good Is winning the battle
if you lose the war?

1248
01:40:13,880 --> 01:40:15,950
Aspetta un momen to.

1249
01:40:16,160 --> 01:40:19,311
Why be miserable
with someone you don't love?

1250
01:40:19,520 --> 01:40:23,354
Betterto be miserable
with someone you do love.

1251
01:40:26,440 --> 01:40:29,318
Hello? Hello.

1252
01:40:29,520 --> 01:40:31,238
Paris.

1253
01:40:31,440 --> 01:40:34,955
Yes, Hotel Deauville.

1254
01:40:37,160 --> 01:40:39,116
Yes, I'll hold on.

1255
01:40:52,680 --> 01:40:55,399
- Miss Fellini. Where...?
- Apartment 2a...

1256
01:40:55,600 --> 01:40:58,478
- Thank you.
- What's she made up for?

1260
01:41:24,480 --> 01:41:27,392
Yes, operator, I'm still holding on.

1261
01:41:27,600 --> 01:41:30,353
Hello? Hello?

1262
01:41:30,560 --> 01:41:31,993
Sandy.

1263
01:41:32,720 --> 01:41:33,994
Hi.

1264
01:41:35,400 --> 01:41:36,879
Oh, It's you.

1265
01:41:37,080 --> 01:41:40,277
Remember I told you
we were going to Paris?

1266
01:41:40,480 --> 01:41:42,152
Did you?

1267
01:41:42,360 --> 01:41:45,557
Well, I couldn’t go.
I didn't have your phone number.

1268
01:41:45,760 --> 01:41:47,113
Oh.

1269
01:41:49,320 --> 01:41:52,039
I suddenly realized
I might never see you again.

1270
01:41:53,200 --> 01:41:55,395
You don’t care
if you never see me again.

1271
01:41:55,600 --> 01:41:58,831
- I don’t want to hurt your feelings.
- Don't say another word.

1272
01:41:59,040 --> 01:42:02,191
Let's have dinner tonight.
The two of us will sit and talk.

1273
01:42:02,400 --> 01:42:05,153
And maybe get to know each other.

1274
01:42:05,360 --> 01:42:07,351
OK?

1276
01:42:11,200 --> 01:42:14,556
- OK?
- What'll I tell Mario?

1277
01:42:15,560 --> 01:42:19,633
- Who's Mario?
- My date for tonight.

1279
01:42:21,600 --> 01:42:23,158
Oh.

1280
01:42:23,360 --> 01:42:25,635
I see.

1281
01:42:25,840 --> 01:42:29,276
Oh, but I can cancel it

1282
01:42:29,480 --> 01:42:31,198
Will you?

1283
01:42:31,400 --> 01:42:34,710
- I won’t even answer the phone.
- Good.

1284
01:42:39,720 --> 01:42:42,473
Promise. I won’t even touch you.

1285
01:43:24,200 --> 01:43:25,872
Robert

1286
01:43:28,320 --> 01:43:29,309
Robert

1287
01:43:29,520 --> 01:43:31,750
There she Is.
I told you she'd be here.

1288
01:43:31,960 --> 01:43:33,393
Robert

1289
01:43:34,760 --> 01:43:35,749
Lisa

1290
01:43:37,200 --> 01:43:40,749
Mi lasci passare.
Un momen to, e che dlavolo!

1291
01:43:40,960 --> 01:43:44,839
Devo parlare con quel signore
che sta prendendo II treno. La prego!

1292
01:43:45,040 --> 01:43:47,554
- Non si può.
- Ho capito, cafone!

1293
01:43:47,760 --> 01:43:51,639
Darling, I knew you wouldn't
let me down. My sisters are over there.

1294
01:43:51,840 --> 01:43:53,512
Robert...

1295
01:43:53,720 --> 01:43:55,631
Robert

1296
01:43:57,760 --> 01:44:00,149
I'm here Robert

1297
01:44:00,360 --> 01:44:03,591
I'll send you both a wedding present

1298
01:44:03,800 --> 01:44:06,075
Andiamo!

1299
01:44:06,280 --> 01:44:07,599
There you are.

1300
01:44:07,800 --> 01:44:10,553
I'll give the fellow credit:
he's a jolly good loser.

1301
01:44:10,760 --> 01:44:13,638
You stop here and don't move.
I'll bring my sisters.

1302
01:44:16,280 --> 01:44:18,669
- Ho detto non si può!
- Ho capito!

1304
01:44:38,240 --> 01:44:41,994
- Ancora lei
- È un padre dl famiglia, mi può capire.

1305
01:44:43,440 --> 01:44:47,797
Mi guardi, sola e abandonata con questo
bambino. Il giorno delle nozze.

1306
01:44:48,000 --> 01:44:50,514
E il padre di questo bambino sta
partendo.

1307
01:44:50,720 --> 01:44:52,517
Mascalzone americano!

1308
01:44:52,720 --> 01:44:54,676
- America no?
- America no d'America.

1309
01:44:54,880 --> 01:44:57,155
Se lei non mi fa
passare, quello lì se ne val

1310
01:45:00,280 --> 01:45:02,396
I can't let you leave
without even talking to her.

1311
01:45:02,600 --> 01:45:05,194
She's got that little something extra.

1312
01:45:08,400 --> 01:45:12,393
That little something extra.
This could never happen In England.

1313
01:45:12,600 --> 01:45:14,477
It's this beastly climate.

1314
01:45:27,320 --> 01:45:29,197
- Eccolo!
- È lui?

1315
01:45:29,400 --> 01:45:33,029
- Il papà.
- L'americano? Ci penso io.

1316
01:45:36,440 --> 01:45:38,396
Guarda papà.

1318
01:46:06,360 --> 01:46:10,558
...nobody's gonna... That's not mine.
I'm gonna leave this country.

1319
01:46:10,760 --> 01:46:13,638
I'm gonna go back to America

1320
01:46:13,840 --> 01:46:15,956
Lisa, tell him I'm not...

1324
01:46:56,600 --> 01:46:59,114
He has done it, again.

1325
01:47:14,560 --> 01:47:16,994
Sir, I thought you were both
on your way to America.

1326
01:47:17,200 --> 01:47:19,714
You've two minutes to get everyone
out of the house.

1327
01:47:19,920 --> 01:47:22,878
I received a letter from Margaret.
She's forgiven me.

1328
01:47:23,080 --> 01:47:25,913
We might even get married.
I needed the money.

1329
01:47:26,120 --> 01:47:27,951
I said Everybody out.

1330
01:47:28,160 --> 01:47:30,833
They’re different, so quiet,
you won't even notice they're around.

1331
01:47:31,040 --> 01:47:34,510
All right. If you won't
throw them out I will.

1332
01:48:06,720 --> 01:48:09,837
Are you sure
those two people are married?

1333
01:48:14,880 --> 01:48:18,395
Sister, this time I'm sure.

